This ansible playbook installs, configs, and spins up nginx on your server.

Prerequisite:

- From the server running this playbook, i.e. the ansible host:

	-- Install Ansible using sudo apt install -y ansible

	-- Create a new directory structure for this project, e.g. mkdir -p nginx_ansible


- To define the target server where nginx is gonna be installed:

	-- under roles/nginx/vars/main.yaml, set SERVER_NAME as the public address of the target

- Make sure the target accept ssh from the ansible host

- Make sure the target accept http from the ansible host to view the generated html page

